565
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:38,239
And a little smashed.

566
00:39:39,199 --> 00:39:40,440
Or at least I think so.

567
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:44,199
-This is what smashed means, right?
-Yeah.

568
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:47,440
-I can tell you are.
-Thanks.

569
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:52,280
So...

570
00:39:53,159 --> 00:39:55,920
Why don't we have a nice glass of water
loaded with ice?

571
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:06,000
Thanks.

572
00:40:11,400 --> 00:40:12,719
-Shall we?
-Let’s.

573
00:40:24,519 --> 00:40:28,119
It came out! Sorry.
It's just that I really love this dress.

574
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:32,039
Though I think it's time to hang it up.
It's very early 2018,

575
00:40:32,119 --> 00:40:34,039
and velvet isn't...

576
00:40:38,719 --> 00:40:40,000
Are you all right?

577
00:40:40,079 --> 00:40:42,199
-What?
-Are you all right?

578
00:40:45,199 --> 00:40:46,880
I don't want to ruin the party for you.

579
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:49,239
That's what my best friend
should be here for,

580
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:51,199
but she left without saying goodbye.

581
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:53,559
I'm here, Lucrecia.

582
00:40:53,639 --> 00:40:57,360
For anything you need.
You can trust me and--

583
00:41:00,079 --> 00:41:01,199
Call me Lu.

584
00:41:03,159 --> 00:41:04,119
Call me Lu.

585
00:41:06,039 --> 00:41:08,519
Is it true?
The thing about the jacket and...

586
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:10,760
the blood?

587
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:13,599
What relationship did you have
with Samuel?

588
00:41:14,199 --> 00:41:15,159
None.

589
00:41:16,079 --> 00:41:19,199
-We hardly spoke.
-Are you sure?

590
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:21,039
Because one of your classmates told us

591
00:41:21,119 --> 00:41:23,800
that you said something to him
in the hall a few weeks ago.

592
00:41:24,199 --> 00:41:25,599
Do you remember what you said?

593
00:41:27,079 --> 00:41:28,880
What did you say to him, Lucrecia?

594
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:33,840
I said, "You're a dead man, you bastard."

595
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:35,719
It's my fault.

596
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:37,800
I left the door wide open
for Miss Palestine.

597
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:40,880
And she has thrown herself
into reconquering him.

598
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:44,000
Lu, you don’t have to look after Guzmán
his entire life.

599
00:41:44,079 --> 00:41:45,599
Anyway, who's looking after you?

600
00:41:46,519 --> 00:41:48,199
So, where are you going?

601
00:41:48,679 --> 00:41:51,800
Our car has arrived, miss.

602
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:54,000
What?

603
00:41:54,079 --> 00:42:00,039
I almost went down,
but I puked a very, very, very little bit,

604
00:42:00,119 --> 00:42:03,880
-and look at me! Now I'm good as new.
-Sure.

605
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:06,519
I bet Luis Miguel makes a song about that.

606
00:42:07,559 --> 00:42:08,440
No.

607
00:42:09,679 --> 00:42:11,440
Don't you want to come with us?

608
00:42:11,519 --> 00:42:13,400
Your house is not too far.

609
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:15,960
No, I already ordered a Cabify.
I think it's this one.

610
00:42:16,039 --> 00:42:17,519
I'll take it and leave.

611
00:42:17,599 --> 00:42:19,320
-Bye, honey.
-See you.

